benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/customFields/search/{searchKey} - Search custom fields

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC04, @TC05, @TC06, @TC07, @TC08, @TC09, @TC10, @TC11, @TC12, @TC13, @TC14, @TC28, @TC29 cover successful retrieval with various parameters.
Empty Response: @TC06 covers no matching records scenario.
Query Parameters: Multiple scenarios test limit, offset, audit, and combinations thereof (@TC02, @TC03, @TC04, @TC05, @TC07, @TC08, @TC09, @TC10, @TC11, @TC12, @TC13, @TC14, @TC28, @TC29).
Error Handling: @TC11, @TC12, @TC13, @TC14, @TC15, @TC16, @TC17, @TC30 cover invalid parameters, authentication failures, backend unavailability, and unsupported methods.
Special Characters & Injection: @TC18 tests special characters in searchKey for XSS/injection vulnerabilities.
Stress & Performance: @TC19, @TC20, @TC23 cover large payloads, concurrency, and data consistency.
Boundary & Unicode: @TC26, @TC27 test maximum length and Unicode characters.
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests for handling pagination beyond limit/offset parameters, such as cursor-based pagination or large dataset performance under load.
Caching Behavior: No tests verify cache headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Rate Limiting: No scenarios simulate rapid multiple requests to test rate limiting or throttling.
Authorization: While authentication failure is tested, authorization levels or permissions are not explicitly tested.
Handling of malformed or unexpected searchKey inputs such as only whitespace or extremely long strings (beyond boundary tests).
Regression for previously fixed bugs related to empty or malformed searchKey inputs is only partially covered.
recommendations: Add explicit tests for cache headers to verify caching behavior.
Include rate limiting and throttling tests to ensure system stability under load.
Test authorization with different user roles and permissions.
Implement boundary tests for maximum searchKey length and unexpected input formats.
Add regression tests for known bugs, especially with empty or malformed searchKey inputs.
Include tests for cursor-based pagination if applicable.
